          <num>17a-862</num>
          <heading>Dementia Services Coordinator. Duties</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Sec. 17a-862. Dementia Services Coordinator. Duties.There shall be within the Department of Aging and Disability Services a dementia services coordinator. The dementia services coordinator shall (1) coordinate dementia services across state agencies, (2) assess and analyze dementia-related data collected by the state, (3) evaluate state-funded dementia services, (4) identify and support the development of dementia-specific training programs, and (5) perform any other relevant duties to support individuals with dementia in the state, as determined by the Commissioner of Aging and Disability Services.
